{"id":"1912.11093","submitter":"Isaac Pesenson Prof.","authors":"Isaac Z. Pesenson","title":"A Weak Weyl's Law on compact metric measure spaces","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.FA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The well known Weyl's Law (Weyl's asymptotic formula) gives an approximation\nto the number $\\mathcal{N}_{\\omega}$ of eigenvalues (counted with\nmultiplicities) on a large interval $[0,\\>\\omega]$ of the Laplace-Beltrami\noperator on a compact Riemannian manifold ${\\bf M}$. In this paper we prove a\nkind of a weak version of the Weyl's law on certain compact metric measure\nspaces ${\\bf X}$ which are equipped with a self-adjoint non-negative operator\n$\\mathcal{L}$ acting in $L_{2}({\\bf X})$.\n  Roughly speaking, we show that if a certain Poincar\\'e inequality holds then\n$\\mathcal{N}_{\\omega}$ is controlled by the cardinality of an appropriate cover\n$\\mathcal{B}_{\\omega^{-1/2}}=\\{B(x_{j},\\omega^{-1/2})\\},\\>\\>\\>x_{j}\\in {\\bf\nX},$ of ${\\bf X}$ by balls of radius $\\omega^{-1/2}$.\n  Moreover, an opposite inequality holds if the heat kernel that corresponds to\n$\\mathcal{L}$ satisfies short time Gaussian estimates.\n  It is known that in the case of the so-called strongly local regular with a\ncomplete intrinsic metric Dirichlet spaces the Poincar\\'e inequality holds iff\nthe corresponding heat kernel satisfies short time Gaussian estimates. Thus for\nsuch spaces one obtains that $\\mathcal{N}_{\\omega}$ is essentially equivalent\nto the cardinality of a cover $\\mathcal{B}_{\\omega^{-1/2}}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Dec 2019 20:10:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-25"}
